<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">One thing that JPMorgan Chase &amp; Co., one o=
f the world=E2=80=99s biggest banks, wants to do is lend money to big corpo=
rate and private equity clients. In many ways,=C2=A0JPMorgan seems well sui=
ted to doing this: As a giant bank with more than $3 trillion of assets, it=
 employs a lot of people who have good relationships with corporate clients=
 and private equity sponsors, a lot of people who advise on the mergers tha=
t create the need for these loans, and a lot of people who are good at maki=
ng credit decisions. But JPMorgan=E2=80=99s ability to lend money to corpor=
ate clients is constrained by a simple problem: <em>Where would it get the =
money? </em></p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Bloomberg=E2=80=99s Gillian Tan and Paula Seli=
gson <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/33234558.2584=
14/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9uZXdzL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjMtMTEtMDEvanBt=
b3JnYW4tanBtLWlzLXNhaWQtdG8tc2Vlay1vdXQtYS1wYXJ0bmVyLWZvci1wcml2YXRlLWNyZWR=
pdC1wdXNoP2NtcGlkPUJCRDExMDIyM19NT05FWVNUVUZGJnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmdXRtX3=
NvdXJjZT1uZXdzbGV0dGVyJnV0bV90ZXJtPTIzMTEwMiZ1dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249bW9uZXlzdHVmZ=
g/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB7ffa2ffd" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"it=
emscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !=
important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-b=
ottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">  report on JPMorgan=E2=80=99s=
 quest</a> to find a source of money that it can lend to clients:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">JPMorgan Chase &amp; Co. is searching for a po=
tential partner to grow its private credit business and accelerate its push=
 into one of the hottest areas in leveraged finance, according to people wi=
th knowledge of the matter.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The discussions with prospective partners =E2=
=80=94 including sovereign wealth funds, pension funds, endowments and alte=
rnative asset managers =E2=80=94 began in recent months and are at an early=
 stage, the people said, asking not to be named discussing a private situat=
ion. The structure and terms of a potential partnership haven=E2=80=99t bee=
n finalized, and it=E2=80=99s possible more than one partner may be selecte=
d. JPMorgan approached some firms and received inbound inquiries from other=
s, one of the people added.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">JPMorgan is looking for third-party capital to=
 supplement the more than $10 billion of balance sheet cash that it has alr=
eady set aside for its private credit strategy, which it began rolling out =
in the last year. A bigger pool of capital would allow the bank to better c=
ompete with heavyweights such as Blackstone Inc., Apollo Global Management =
Inc. and Ares Management Corp. by making larger commitments or participatin=
g in larger deals. =E2=80=A6</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Wall Street banks are trying to figure out the=
 best way to compete with private credit, which is eating into the market s=
hare of the leveraged loan and high-yield bond markets, a key fee generator=
. Investment banks typically sell junk-rated debt to large groups of instit=
utional asset managers, rather than hold the risk on their balance sheet, w=
hereas private credit lenders are specialized asset-management firms that o=
riginate the loans directly from their own funds. Efforts by banks to compe=
te off their own balance sheets is a return to traditional lending but come=
s with a high capital charge for those loans.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I am being stupid. But I do think that it is w=
orth noticing how strange this is. In the olden days banks took deposits an=
d made loans. This is a notably risky business model, for reasons that ever=
yone knows and that <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/clic=
k/33234558.258414/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzL=
zIwMjMtMDMtMTAvc3RhcnR1cC1iYW5rLWhhZC1hLXN0YXJ0dXAtYmFuay1ydW4_Y21waWQ9QkJE=
MTEwMjIzX01PTkVZU1RVRkYmdXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc291cmNlPW5ld3NsZXR0ZXI=
mdXRtX3Rlcm09MjMxMTAyJnV0bV9jYW1wYWlnbj1tb25leXN0dWZm/607f07ceef4b8524a319a=
23cB295483fa" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_bla=
nk" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-botto=
m-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; bac=
kground-color: #ccc;">  we</a> have <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergb=
usiness.com/click/33234558.258414/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGlua=
W9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjMtMDUtMDQvbm9ib2R5LXRydXN0cy10aGUtYmFua3Mtbm93P2NtcGlk=
PUJCRDExMDIyM19NT05FWVNUVUZGJnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmdXRtX3NvdXJjZT1uZXdzbGV=
0dGVyJnV0bV90ZXJtPTIzMTEwMiZ1dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249bW9uZXlzdHVmZg/607f07ceef4b852=
4a319a23cB05f31b62" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=
=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; bord=
er-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: so=
lid; background-color: #ccc;">  discussed</a> a <a href=3D"https://link.mai=
l.bloombergbusiness.com/click/33234558.258414/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnL=
mNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjMtMDUtMDkvaXQtcy1uZXZlci10b28tbGF0ZS1mb3It=
YmFua3MtdG8taGVkZ2U_Y21waWQ9QkJEMTEwMjIzX01PTkVZU1RVRkYmdXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWF=
pbCZ1dG1fc291cmNlPW5ld3NsZXR0ZXImdXRtX3Rlcm09MjMxMTAyJnV0bV9jYW1wYWlnbj1tb2=
5leXN0dWZm/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBa93842a1" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemsc=
ope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoratio=
n: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000;=
 border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">  lot</a> this year: =
The deposits are short-term, the loans are long-term, and if all the deposi=
tors want their money back at once, the bank can=E2=80=99t get it all back =
at once from the borrowers. In 2023 banks still, absolutely, take deposits =
and make loans, but everyone sort of knows to be nervous about it. One way =
that=C2=A0<em>regulators=C2=A0</em>express nervousness about it is by impos=
ing high capital requirements on illiquid loans made by banks.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">And so if JPMorgan executives get together and=
 say =E2=80=9Chey, we have a huge competitive risk and opportunity here, a =
lot of our best corporate and private-equity clients really want to borrow =
money from us, and if we lend them money we=E2=80=99ll get really good risk=
-adjusted returns, but if we don=E2=80=99t we will lose business to competi=
tors, so let=E2=80=99s do it,=E2=80=9D and someone asks =E2=80=9Cokay but h=
ow should we fund these loans to our clients,=E2=80=9D and someone answers =
=E2=80=9Cwell, just spitballing here, but we could use our customers=E2=80=
=99 deposits to make the loans,=E2=80=9D that would be, like, shocking? You=
 don=E2=80=99t just go around=C2=A0<em>saying </em>=E2=80=9Clet=E2=80=99s u=
se customer deposits to make long-term loans to risky borrowers=E2=80=9D! L=
ook where that got Sam Bankman-Fried!</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">No, the correct answer is =E2=80=9Clet=E2=80=
=99s go partner with a pension fund or sovereign wealth fund, someone who h=
as really long-term capital that they can commit to this business while we =
manage it.=E2=80=9D Or, I mean, to be fair, the actual answer is some of bo=
th; JPMorgan is using =E2=80=9Cmore than $10 billion of balance sheet cash=
=E2=80=9D alongside whatever it can raise from partners.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">We have <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloomberg=
business.com/click/33234558.258414/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGlu=
aW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjMtMDUtMTEvYmxhY2tzdG9uZS1jYW4tYmUtdGhlLWJhbms_Y21waWQ=
9QkJEMTEwMjIzX01PTkVZU1RVRkYmdXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc291cmNlPW5ld3NsZX=
R0ZXImdXRtX3Rlcm09MjMxMTAyJnV0bV9jYW1wYWlnbj1tb25leXN0dWZm/607f07ceef4b8524=
a319a23cB5230158c" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D=
"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-=
bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid=
; background-color: #ccc;">  talked</a> a number of <a href=3D"https://link=
.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/33234558.258414/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZ=
XJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjMtMDQtMjAvYmFua2luZy1nZXRzLWEtYml0LW5h=
cnJvd2VyP2NtcGlkPUJCRDExMDIyM19NT05FWVNUVUZGJnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmdXRtX3N=
vdXJjZT1uZXdzbGV0dGVyJnV0bV90ZXJtPTIzMTEwMiZ1dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249bW9uZXlzdHVmZg=
/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBf4d527c7" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"ite=
mscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !i=
mportant; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bo=
ttom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">  times</a> around <a href=3D"h=
ttps://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/33234558.258414/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3=
cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjMtMTAtMzEvYmFkLXBhc3N3b3Jkc=
y1hcmUtc2VjdXJpdGllcy1mcmF1ZD9jbXBpZD1CQkQxMTAyMjNfTU9ORVlTVFVGRiZ1dG1fbWVk=
aXVtPWVtYWlsJnV0bV9zb3VyY2U9bmV3c2xldHRlciZ1dG1fdGVybT0yMzExMDImdXRtX2NhbXB=
haWduPW1vbmV5c3R1ZmY/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBa5aaeda2" itemprop=3D"StoryLi=
nk" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text=
-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color=
: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">  here</a> =
about this basic idea, that private credit is increasingly substituting for=
 bank loans because it has a better funding model. Pension funds, insurance=
 companies, sovereign wealth funds and the alternative asset managers that =
do private credit investing for them have very stable long-term funding; US=
 regional banks have flighty short-term deposits. Private credit is a form =
of =E2=80=9Cnarrow banking,=E2=80=9D a model in which banks invest deposits=
 at the Fed and lending is done by specialized firms with long-term equity =
funding. The specialized firms are private-credit managers, and the long-te=
rm funding comes from pensions.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">But it is not just US regional banks with flig=
hty deposits; it=E2=80=99s global megabanks with sticky deposits too. Even =
at JPMorgan, there is a push to make banking narrower.</p>
