<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I think of artificial intelligence in finance =
as having two main approaches. <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusine=
ss.com/click/33234558.258414/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2=
FydGljbGVzLzIwMjMtMTAtMDMvdGhlLXNlYy1oYWQtYS1idXN5LXdlZWs_Y21waWQ9QkJEMTEwM=
jIzX01PTkVZU1RVRkYmdXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc291cmNlPW5ld3NsZXR0ZXImdXRt=
X3Rlcm09MjMxMTAyJnV0bV9jYW1wYWlnbj1tb25leXN0dWZm/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB1=
dd4c6fd" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" s=
tyle=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-wid=
th: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; backgrou=
nd-color: #ccc;">  One is</a>: You apply artificial intelligence to financi=
al data. You get some neural nets, you get some data, you train the neural =
nets on the data, they spot predictive patterns in the data, those patterns=
 generate trade ideas, you do them, you hope they make money.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The other is: There are general-purpose large =
language models that can, in certain domains and with certain constraints, =
produce text that a smart human might have written. Why not use them to do =
the work that a human investment analyst would do? Train them on some corpu=
s of language, including earnings calls and 10-Ks and finance textbooks and=
 Warren Buffett=E2=80=99s annual letters but also, like, Twitter and <em>Mo=
by-Dick</em>, and then type in the little box =E2=80=9Crecommend five stock=
s that will go up a lot, and give your reasons,=E2=80=9D and see what they =
come up with. If it=E2=80=99s persuasive, buy the stocks. If it=E2=80=99s n=
ot, yell at the chatbot, in the little box, until it does a better job. Or =
type =E2=80=9Cexplain what the Fed=E2=80=99s decision yesterday means for f=
inancial markets=E2=80=9D and get a long nuanced report that informs your i=
nvestment decisions. You make the investment decisions =E2=80=94=C2=A0not t=
he chatbot =E2=80=94=C2=A0but the chatbot=E2=80=99s work helps support them=
. The chatbot is an analyst, one who is cheap and tireless and broadly info=
rmed about the world, but also one without a ton of domain-specific experti=
se, with weird and unpredictable gaps in its knowledge, and with a propensi=
ty for making stuff up. It=E2=80=99s not the most reliable analyst! You wou=
ldn=E2=80=99t let it trade on its own! But it could, with careful supervisi=
on, help.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The problem with the first form of AI is that =
you have to have a lot of expertise =E2=80=94=C2=A0at building AI models an=
d collecting data =E2=80=94=C2=A0to have a real shot at using it successful=
ly. Also it has a tendency to produce =E2=80=9Cblack box=E2=80=9D investmen=
ts, where the AI knows why it is buying the stuff it is buying, but you don=
=E2=80=99t, and the AI can=E2=80=99t tell you. =E2=80=9CI am using 35,000 s=
ignals each with a weight that shifts as market conditions change, don=E2=
=80=99t worry about it,=E2=80=9D the AI tells you, and you=E2=80=99re like =
=E2=80=9Cfine I guess.=E2=80=9D And maybe it works great forever and you ge=
t rich, and maybe the AI is just overfitting to recent events and it blows =
up.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Whereas the ChatGPT model, like, you can just =
get that online, and type your question in the little box, and ChatGPT tell=
s you its reasons for recommending whatever it is recommending, and you can=
 read them and decide if they are persuasive or not. It=E2=80=99s a very hu=
man-scale way to use AI in investing.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">If you want to hire ChatGPT as your cheap, som=
ewhat unreliable analyst, one question you might ask is: Is this analyst a =
Chartered Financial Analyst charterholder?<a class=3D"footnote-index" href=
=3D"#footnote-1" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important;=
 border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-styl=
e: none !important; background-color: transparent !important; display: inli=
ne-block;">
<span>[1]</span>
</a>=C2=A0Would you ask that question? I don=E2=80=99t know. In any case,=
=C2=A0Bloomberg=E2=80=99s William Shaw and Emily Graffeo provide the answer=
, <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/33234558.258414/=
aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9uZXdzL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjMtMTEtMDIvY2FuLWN=
oYXRncHQtcGFzcy10aGUtY2ZhLWV4YW0tYWktcmVzZWFyY2hlcnMtdHJpZWQtdG8tZmluZC1vdX=
Q_Y21waWQ9QkJEMTEwMjIzX01PTkVZU1RVRkYmdXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc291cmNlP=
W5ld3NsZXR0ZXImdXRtX3Rlcm09MjMxMTAyJnV0bV9jYW1wYWlnbj1tb25leXN0dWZm/607f07c=
eef4b8524a319a23cBbe0fde8d" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" =
target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important=
; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-sty=
le: solid; background-color: #ccc;">  which is no</a>:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Relax, Wall Street. ChatGPT is still a ways of=
f from passing the chartered financial analyst exam and threatening the job=
s of financial professionals the world over.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">A team of JPMorgan Chase &amp; Co. researchers=
 and university academics tested whether OpenAI=E2=80=99s ChatGPT and GPT-4=
 chatbots would have a chance at passing the first two levels of the exam. =
It typically takes humans four years to complete all three levels of the te=
st, which can lead to higher salaries and better job opportunities.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CBased on estimated pass rates and ave=
rage self-reported scores, we concluded that ChatGPT would likely not be ab=
le to pass the CFA Level I and Level II under all tested settings,=E2=80=9D=
 the researchers wrote in an 11-page report. =E2=80=9CGPT-4 would have a de=
cent chance of passing the CFA Level I and Level II if prompted.=E2=80=9D</=
p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Okay. ChatGPT: Good at saying stuff, less good=
 at factual domain-specific knowledge. There is also a fun quote from Chris=
 Wiese of the CFA Institute suggesting that robots are not welcome:</p>
<blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CWhile multiple choice exa=
ms and essay questions remain excellent ways to assess learning and underst=
anding in a secure proctored environment, the day-to-day in finance does no=
t present itself only as a series of short, standalone questions,=E2=80=9D =
Wiese said. =E2=80=9CThis is why to become a CFA charterholder, we also req=
uire 4,000 hours of qualifying work experience, a minimum of two references=
, a strong moral compass, and, coming soon, the completion of hands-on prac=
tical skills modules.=E2=80=9D</p></blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">ChatGPT could never pass the strong moral comp=
ass requirement! Or at least it could never pass the hands-on practical ski=
lls modules. No hands.</p>
