state might end up raising enough money to pay back all the customers.<a cl=
ass=3D"footnote-index" href=3D"#footnote-3" style=3D"color: #000000; text-d=
ecoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: =
#000000; border-bottom-style: none !important; background-color: transparen=
t !important; display: inline-block;">
<span>[3]</span>
</a></p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">And then I suppose Bankman-Fried could go to t=
he judge and say =E2=80=9Clook, sure, the prosecutors say that I=C2=A0<em>i=
ntended=C2=A0</em>to steal $8 billion from customers, and on the objective =
facts it seems like that is what I intended. But I failed! Somehow all of m=
y stealing from customers ended up with them getting all their money back. =
So no loss, no theft, no harm, no foul. So just give me six months of house=
 arrest.=E2=80=9D=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">This will not work, for him, even a little bit=
. Still the law is interesting.</p>
