<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The basic mechanism of a lot of decentralized =
finance projects is=C2=A0a=C2=A0Ponzi scheme with some fairly standard comp=
lexification:</p>
<ol style=3D"list-style-type: decimal; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;"=
>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">You invent a token, BoxCoin or whatev=
er,<a class=3D"footnote-index" href=3D"#footnote-7" style=3D"color: #000000=
; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom=
-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: none !important; background-color: tr=
ansparent !important; display: inline-block;">
<span>[7]</span>
</a>=C2=A0and sell it to people.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">P=
eople who own BoxCoin get paid a yield =E2=80=94=C2=A0=E2=80=9CAPY,=E2=80=
=9D for =E2=80=9Cannual percentage yield,=E2=80=9D is the standard term =E2=
=80=94=C2=A0<em>in BoxCoin</em>, or perhaps in some related crypto token.</=
li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Like, you know, every 12 hours you =
get 10% more tokens or whatever.=C2=A0</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5=
px;">People are like =E2=80=9Clook at how high the yield on BoxCoin is, I=
=E2=80=99d better get some.=E2=80=9D</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px=
;">They buy it, and the price goes up.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5=
px;">Now the yield looks even better: Now you have 100 BoxCoins worth, like=
, 2 cents each, but in 12 hours you=E2=80=99ll have 110 BoxCoins worth 3 ce=
nts each. What a yield!</li>
</ol>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The trick is =E2=80=A6=C2=A0I mean, it is all =
a trick =E2=80=A6=C2=A0but one trick is to hype it up and=C2=A0get people t=
o buy BoxCoins, so that yield looks like an actual monetary yield rather th=
an just the proliferation of worthless numbers, and the other trick is to g=
et people not to=C2=A0<em>sell=C2=A0</em>BoxCoins, because if they sell it =
all collapses.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">We have talked about this so many times. This =
