<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Anyway SafeMoon=E2=80=99s=C2=A0trick was that =
if you sold your SafeMoon tokens, the SafeMoon protocol would take a 10% =
=E2=80=9Ctax.=E2=80=9D Thus buying was good and selling was bad, which kept=
 a floor on the price. (For a while.) Half of the 10% tax was used to pay t=
he yield on the other tokens: If you=C2=A0<em>sell=C2=A0</em>your tokens, y=
ou pay 10%; if you=C2=A0<em>hold=C2=A0</em>your tokens, you get half of the=
 money that the sellers pay. This creates a further incentive to hold, and =
the yield that makes the whole thing attractive. This was called =E2=80=9Cr=
eflection=E2=80=9D; SafeMoon=E2=80=99s <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombe=
rgbusiness.com/click/33234558.258414/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2VjLmdvdi9maWxlcy9saX=
